21/09/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Defence Minister Pandeli Majko met with visiting Italian military attorney General Giuseppe Scandurra on Friday (19 September).
Majko stressed the importance of enhancing co-operation in the sphere of military legislation, and briefed Scandurra on legislation aimed at reforming the Albanian armed forces.
Scandurra, in turn, said the purpose of his five-day visit is to boost collaboration between the military prosecution offices of the two countries.
He also met with Albanian Attorney General Thedhori Sollaku as well as President Alfred Moisiu and Armed Forces Chief of Staff Major General Pellumb Qazimi.
(ATA, BBC - 19/09/03)
